> Here's the setup.  Solaris 2.5 machine as NFS server,
Oh dear 8)
> Linux 2.2.5 machine as NFS client.  When compiling
> something on Linux machine, some output files get corrupted.
> The above is the only server-client combination for which
> data corruption is observed.
You need to visit Sunsolve for that paticular bug I suspect. There is a problem
with Solaris 2.5 (and I believe 2.5.1) where NFS corruption occurs with data
1-3 bytes offset on some I/O patterns generally generated by the gnu linker.
Sunsolve should have the fix on it.
